%N A134991 Triangle of Ward numbers T(n,k) read by rows.
%C A134991 This is the triangle of associated Stirling numbers of the second kind, A008299, read along the diagonals.
%C A134991 This is also a row-reversed version of A181996 (with an additional leading 1) - see the table on p. 92 in the Ward reference. A134685 is a refinement of the Ward table.
%C A134991 The first and second diagonals are A001147 and A000457 and appear in the diagonals of several OEIS entries. The polynomials also appear in Carlitz (p. 85), Drake et al. (p. 8) and Smiley (p. 7).
%C A134991 First few polynomials (with a different offset) are
%C A134991   P(0,t) = 0
%C A134991   P(1,t) = 1
%C A134991   P(2,t) = t
%C A134991   P(3,t) = t + 3*t^2
%C A134991   P(4,t) = t + 10*t^2 + 15*t^3
%C A134991   P(5,t) = t + 25*t^2 + 105*t^3 + 105*t^4
%C A134991 These are the "face" numbers of the tropical Grassmannian G(2,n),related to phylogenetic trees (with offset 0 beginning with P(2,t)). Corresponding h-vectors are A008517. - _Tom Copeland_, Oct 03 2011
%C A134991 A133314 applied to the derivative of A(x,t) implies (a.+b.)^n = 0^n, for (b_n)=P(n+1,t) and (a_0)=1, (a_1)=-t, and (a_n)=-(1+t) P(n,t) otherwise. E.g., umbrally, (a.+b.)^2 = a_2*b_0 + 2 a_1*b_1 + a_0*b_2 = 0. - _Tom Copeland_, Oct 08 2011
%C A134991 Beginning with the second column, the rows give the faces of the Whitehouse simplicial complex with the fourth-order complex being three isolated vertices and the fifth-order being the Petersen graph with 10 vertices and 15 edges (cf. Readdy). - _Tom Copeland_, Oct 03 2014
%C A134991 Stratifications of smooth projective varieties which are fine moduli spaces for stable n-pointed rational curves. Cf. pages 20 and 30 of the Kock and Vainsencher reference and references in A134685. - _Tom Copeland_, May 18 2017
%C A134991 Named after the American mathematician Morgan Ward (1901-1963). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 26 2021
