%F A134991 E.g.f. for the polynomials is A(x,t) = (x-t)/(t+1) + T{ (t/(t+1)) * exp[(x-t)/(t+1)] }, where T(x) is the Tree function, the e.g.f. of A000169. The compositional inverse in x (about x = 0) is B(x) = x + -t * [exp(x) - x - 1]. Special case t = 1 gives e.g.f. for A000311. These results are a special case of A134685 with u(x) = B(x).
%F A134991 From _Tom Copeland_, Oct 26 2008: (Start)
%F A134991 Umbral-Sheffer formalism gives, for m a positive integer and u = t/(t+1),
%F A134991 [P(.,t)+Q(.,x)]^m = [m Q(m-1,x) - t Q(m,x)]/(t+1) + sum(n>=1) { n^(n-1)[u exp(-u)]^n/n! [n/(t+1)+Q(.,x)]^m }, when the series is convergent for a sequence of functions Q(n,x).
%F A134991 Check: With t=1; Q(n,x)=0^n, for n>=0; and Q(-1,x)=0, then [P(.,1)+Q(.,x)]^m = P(m,1) = A000311(m).
%F A134991 (End)
%F A134991 Let h(x,t) = 1/(dB(x)/dx) = 1/(1-t*(exp(x)-1)), an e.g.f. in x for row polynomials in t of A019538, then the n-th row polynomial in t of the table A134991, P(n,t), is given by ((h(x,t)*d/dx)^n)x evaluated at x=0, i.e., A(x,t) = exp(x*P(.,t)) = exp(x*h(u,t)*d/du) u evaluated at u=0. Also, dA(x,t)/dx = h(A(x,t),t). - _Tom Copeland_, Sep 05 2011
%F A134991 The polynomials (1+t)/t*P(n,t) are the row polynomials of A112493. Let f(x) = (1+x)/(1-x*t). Then for n >= 0, P(n+1,t) is given by t/(1+t)*(f(x)*d/dx)^n(f(x)) evaluated at x = 0. - _Peter Bala_, Sep 30 2011
%F A134991 From _Tom Copeland_, Oct 04 2011: (Start)
%F A134991 T(n,k) = (k+1)*T(n-1,k) + (n+k+1)*T(n-1,k-1) with starting indices n=0 and k=0 beginning with P(2,t) (as suggested by a formula of David Speyer on MathOverflow).
%F A134991 T(n,k) = k*T(n-1,k) + (n+k-1)*T(n-1,k-1) with starting indices n=1 and k=1 of table (cf. Smiley above and Riordin ref.[10] therein).
%F A134991 P(n,t) = (1/(1+t))^n * Sum_{k>=1} k^(n+k-1)*(u*exp(-u))^k / k! with u=(t/(t+1)) for n>1; therefore, Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^k k^(n+k-1) x^k/k! = [1+LW(x)]^(-n) P{n,-LW(x)/[1+LW(x)]}, with LW(x) the Lambert W-Fct.
%F A134991 T(n,k) = Sum_{i=0..k} ((-1)^i binomial(n+k,i) Sum_{j=0..k-i} (-1)^j (k-i-j)^(n+k-i)/(j!(k-i-j)!)) from relation to A008299. (End)
%F A134991 The e.g.f. A(x,t) = -v * ( Sum_{j=>1} D(j-1,u) (-z)^j / j! ) where u = (x-t)/(1+t), v = 1+u, z = x/((1+t) v^2) and D(j-1,u) are the polynomials of A042977. dA/dx = 1/((1+t)(v-A)) = 1/(1-t*(exp(A)-1)). - _Tom Copeland_, Oct 06 2011
%F A134991 The general results on the convolution of the refined partition polynomials of A134685, with u_1 = 1 and u_n = -t otherwise, can be applied here to obtain results of convolutions of these polynomials. - _Tom Copeland_, Sep 20 2016
%F A134991 E.g.f.: C(u,t) = (u-t)/(1+t) - W( -((t*exp((u-t)/(1+t)))/(1+t)) ), where W is the principal value of the Lambert W-function. - _Cheng Peng_, Sep 11 2021
%F A134991 The function C(u,t) in the previous formula by Peng is precisely the function A(u,t) given in the initial 2008 formula of this section and the Oct 06 2011 formula from Copeland. As noted in A000169, Euler's tree function is T(x) = -LambertW(-x), where W(x) is the principal branch of Lambert's function, and T(x) is the e.g.f. of A000169. - _Tom Copeland_, May 13 2022
